# TravelPlan: Frankfurt to New York Business Trip, June 15–17, 2026

| Day 1 — 2026-06-15 — Arrival and client dinner | Day 2 — 2026-06-16 — Business meetings and client dinner | Day 3 — 2026-06-17 — Final meetings and return flight |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **1. Condor DE2016 flight: Frankfurt to New York JFK** [transport] 11:40–14:25 @ Frankfurt Airport Terminal 1 → JFK Airport (€330.00) — Direct transatlantic flight selected for the business trip: Condor DE 2016 from Frankfurt (FRA) Terminal 1 to New York JFK. Scheduled 11:40 CEST departure and 14:25 EDT arrival; duration shown by flight search as 525 minutes. JFK arrival terminal may be Terminal 7 or Terminal 6 depending on Condor’s 2026 move, so verify 24 hours before travel. — Links: [link 1](https://www.google.com/travel/flights?hl=en&gl=us&curr=EUR&tfs=CBwQAhoeEgoyMDI2LTA2LTE1agcIARIDRlJBcgcIARIDSkZLGh4SCjIwMjYtMDYtMTdqBwgBEgNKRktyBwgBEgNGUkFAAUgBcAGYAQE&tfu=EgIIAQ), [link 2](https://www.flightaware.com/live/flight/CFG2016), [link 3](https://aviability.com/en/flight/de2016-condor) | **1. Hotel breakfast / meeting prep** [meal] 07:30–08:30 @ Park Terrace Hotel on Bryant Park, 18 W 40th St, New York, NY 10018 (€35.00) — Breakfast and preparation time at or near the hotel before meetings. The hotel’s Terrazzo Lounge has been reported as serving breakfast in the morning, but hours should be confirmed at check-in. — Links: [link 1](https://parkterracehotel.com/) | **1. Hotel breakfast and checkout prep** [meal] 07:30–08:30 @ Park Terrace Hotel on Bryant Park, 18 W 40th St, New York, NY 10018 (€35.00) — Breakfast and packing before final meetings. Keep luggage at the hotel after checkout if needed. — Links: [link 1](https://parkterracehotel.com/) |
| **2. Private car/taxi transfer: JFK to Park Terrace Hotel** [transport] 15:30–16:30 @ JFK Airport → Park Terrace Hotel, 18 W 40th St, New York, NY 10018 (€95.00) — Door-to-door transfer from JFK to Midtown after immigration and baggage. Typical taxi/private-car timing to Bryant Park is about 45–60 minutes in standard NYC traffic; choose taxi or pre-booked private transfer for business reliability. — Links: [link 1](https://www.uber.com/global/en/r/routes/jfk-to-bryant-park/), [link 2](https://www.rome2rio.com/s/New-York-JFK-Airport-JFK/Bryant-Park-Hotel-New-York) | **2. Morning business meetings** [other] 09:00–11:30 @ Midtown Manhattan / client offices — Reserved working block for meetings in Midtown Manhattan. Hotel location near Bryant Park/Grand Central keeps most central offices reachable quickly. | **2. Final business meetings** [other] 09:00–10:30 @ Midtown Manhattan / client offices — Short final meeting block before departure to JFK. Keep schedule conservative to protect the international flight check-in window. |
| **3. Check in: Park Terrace Hotel on Bryant Park** [lodging] 16:30–17:00 @ Park Terrace Hotel, 18 W 40th St, New York, NY 10018 (€1174.00) — Check in at a central Midtown business hotel directly by Bryant Park, close to subway lines and Grand Central. Selected for business location over cheaper alternatives. Facilities listed in hotel search include restaurant, non-smoking rooms, fitness facilities, safety deposit box, and housekeeping on request. — Links: [link 1](https://travelstack.nuitee.link/hotels/lpa5464?checkin=2026-06-15&checkout=2026-06-17&rooms=1&adults=1&occupancies=W3siYWR1bHRzIjoxLCJjaGlsZHJlbiI6W119XQ%3D%3D&language=de&currency=EUR), [link 2](https://parkterracehotel.com/) | **3. Business lunch: The Modern Dining Room** [meal] 12:00–14:00 @ The Modern, 9 W 53rd St, New York, NY 10019 (€220.00) — Refined Michelin-starred Midtown lunch at The Modern, suitable for a high-stakes business discussion. Lunch service is Monday–Saturday, 12:00 PM–2:30 PM; reservations open 28 days in advance at 12:00 PM ET. — Links: [link 1](https://www.themodernnyc.com/reservations-11/), [link 2](https://www.opentable.com/r/the-modern-dining-room) | **3. Check out: Park Terrace Hotel** [lodging] 10:30–11:00 @ Park Terrace Hotel, 18 W 40th St, New York, NY 10018 — Check out of Park Terrace Hotel and retrieve luggage. Verified checkout sources vary between 11:00 AM and noon; this slot uses the earlier time to be safe. — Links: [link 1](https://parkterracehotel.com/contact/) |
| **4. Client dinner: STK Steakhouse Midtown** [meal] 19:30–21:30 @ STK Steakhouse Midtown, 1114 Avenue of the Americas, New York, NY 10036 (€160.00) — High-end steakhouse dinner suitable for a professional client meeting. STK Midtown is very close to the hotel/Bryant Park area and open Monday 11:00 AM–11:00 PM. Reserve ahead via the official site/OpenTable; private dining is available for larger client groups. — Links: [link 1](https://stksteakhouse.com/venues/nyc-midtown/), [link 2](https://stksteakhouse.com/en-us/location/nyc-midtown/) | **4. Afternoon business meetings / work block** [other] 14:30–17:30 @ Midtown Manhattan / client offices — Reserved afternoon block for client meetings, calls, or focused work. The hotel and Midtown location keep this logistically efficient. | **4. Early business lunch: Bryant Park Grill** [meal] 11:30–12:30 @ Bryant Park Grill, 25 W 40th St, New York, NY 10018 (€90.00) — Convenient business lunch directly at Bryant Park before departure. Lunch service runs daily 11:30 AM–3:30 PM; reservations recommended for the main dining room. — Links: [link 1](https://bryantparkgrillnyc.com/), [link 2](https://bryantparkgrillnyc.com/menus_cat/garden-lunch-menu/) |
|  | **5. Transfer to West Village client dinner** [transport] 18:30–19:10 @ Park Terrace Hotel → Boucherie West Village, 99 7th Ave S (€35.00) — Taxi/private car from Park Terrace Hotel/Midtown to Boucherie West Village. Routing API was unavailable; based on Manhattan traffic and location, allocate about 25–40 minutes for this crosstown/downtown transfer. — Links: [link 1](https://www.boucherieus.com/west-village-ny-reservations/) | **5. Private car/taxi transfer: Midtown to JFK Terminal 1** [transport] 12:30–13:30 @ Park Terrace Hotel / Bryant Park → JFK Terminal 1 (€95.00) — Depart Midtown for JFK Terminal 1 for Lufthansa LH401. Web-verified typical taxi timing is about 45–60 minutes, with peak traffic risk; this timing targets arrival roughly 2 hours before departure. — Links: [link 1](https://www.rome2rio.com/s/Bryant-Park/JFK-Airport-Terminal-4), [link 2](https://www.shuttlefinder.com/jfk/l/bryant-park) |
|  | **6. Client dinner: Boucherie West Village** [meal] 19:30–21:30 @ Boucherie West Village, 99 7th Ave S, New York, NY 10014 (€150.00) — Upscale French brasserie dinner in the West Village. Open Tuesday 11:00 AM–12:00 AM; reservations are highly recommended via the official site/OpenTable/Resy. Professional but less formal than STK, with strong client-dinner appeal. — Links: [link 1](https://www.boucherieus.com/west-village-menus/), [link 2](https://www.boucherieus.com/west-village-ny-reservations/), [link 3](https://www.opentable.com/r/boucherie-new-york) | **6. JFK Terminal 1 check-in / Lufthansa lounge buffer** [leisure] 13:30–15:10 @ JFK Terminal 1, Lufthansa check-in and lounge (€50.00) — Check in, clear security, and use the Lufthansa Business/Senator Lounge if eligible. Lufthansa LH401 departs from JFK Terminal 1; lounge access is available to eligible Business/First/Star Alliance Gold passengers and may be purchasable subject to availability. — Links: [link 1](https://aviability.com/en/flight/lh401-lufthansa/jfk-fra) |
|  | **7. Return transfer to hotel** [transport] 21:30–22:10 @ Boucherie West Village → Park Terrace Hotel on Bryant Park (€35.00) — Taxi/private car back to Park Terrace Hotel after client dinner. | **7. Lufthansa LH401 return flight: New York JFK to Frankfurt** [transport] 2026-06-17 15:40–2026-06-18 05:25 @ JFK Terminal 1 → Frankfurt Airport (€330.00) — Direct return flight from New York JFK to Frankfurt: Lufthansa LH 401. Flight search shows 465 minutes airborne/elapsed and scheduled arrival in Frankfurt the next morning. Departs JFK Terminal 1. — Links: [link 1](https://www.google.com/travel/flights?hl=en&gl=us&curr=EUR&tfs=CBwQAhoeEgoyMDI2LTA2LTE1agcIARIDRlJBcgcIARIDSkZLGh4SCjIwMjYtMDYtMTdqBwgBEgNKRktyBwgBEgNGUkFAAUgBcAGYAQE&tfu=EgIIAQ), [link 2](https://aviability.com/en/flight/lh401-lufthansa/jfk-fra) |

